profile_positions.description:
Commissioning and Start-up Engineer for Refinery Expansion Project (REP)
-Managing and execute various project EPC activities concerning mechanical equipment (static, rotating, packaging);
-Ensuring necessary coordination with EPC contractors, PMC consultants, including the provision of necessary inputs and engineering deliverable;
-Coordinating all the activities related to the main compressors K-3001A,B / K-3002A,B / K-5301 / K-5302, start-up and performance test;
-providing technical assistance to Operation and trouble-shooting to difficult start-up and run tests

1.Created Preventive Maintenance Master Plan and Schedule, maintenance procedures, working instructions and methods related to rotating equipment;
2.Created Preventive Maintenance strategies for rotating equipment based on Criticality Matrix and Asset Management Standards (ISO 55000 and PAS55) in cooperation with Marco van der Hout (NOIL MM);
3.Performed Criticality Study for ranking all rotating equipment to be used for preventive maintenance master plan and schedule (cooperation with Neste Oil Finland);
4.Responded to breakdowns, evaluate and diagnosed faults, found best repair solutions and assisted repairing activities related to critical equipment;
5.Offered technical expertise to maintenance supervisor, foreman and technicians during repairing activities;
6.Evaluated, expertise and repair the damaged foundation of the GE-NP Recycle Gas reciprocating compressors (in cooperation with EMHA NV);
7.Evaluated, expertise and repair the piping system belong GE-NP Recycle Gas reciprocating compressor affected by high vibration (cooperation with Technip Rome);
8.Evaluated, expertise and improve the design for the suction/discharge valves and packing rod for GE-NP compressors (H2S and Recycle Gas)in cooperation with NP Firenze and Cozzani-Italy;
9.Evaluated, expertise and found solutions for MIC corrosion inside of Emergency Safety Shower piping system;
10.Evaluated, expertise and repair Emergency Release Coupling- components and performed detailed maintenance to the Kanon marine loading arms;
11.Offered technical expertise for B&KV vibration monitoring system used for daily evaluation of health of reciprocating compressors;
12.Implemented SKF @ptitude Analyst system for Machine Condition Monitoring and used within preventive maintenance program based on Asset Condition Monitoring (cooperation with Neste-Oil Finland and SKF).

1.Coordinated pre-commissioning team (4 supervisor and 17 technicians) of Technip-IREM during B2G project execution;
2.Coordinated all the vendor representatives during pre-commissioning, site tests and activities;
3.Created and executed the Master Schedule Plan for pre-commissioning of 976 rotating equipment and  electrical motors (3 GE-NP reciprocating compressors, 1 Neumann-Esser reciprocating compressor, 7 air compressor Ingersoll Rand, 317 process pumps (Flowserve, KSB, MiltonRoy, Weir Gabbioneta ,etc., 20 submersible sump pump, 20 side mixers Milton Roy, 46 top side mixers, 22 air fin fan coolers, 570 different power-electric motors);
4.Prepared, implemented and supervised application of pre-comm procedures, work instruction and alignment methods used for all specific rotating equipment;
5.Prepared, implemented and supervised application of pre-comm procedures, work instruction and alignment methods used for all specific rotating equipment;
6.Offered technical engineering expertise to the Technip / IREM supervisor, IREM / RES foreman and technicians during execution of pre-commissioning, commissioning and start-up  activities related to the rotating equipment;
7.Responding to faults found in execution of pre-commissionning and start-up activities, analyzed and found best technical solution and supervised execution;
8.Supervised all the Solo-Run test performed with electrical motors and prepared all the handover documents;
9.Supervised all the activities connected to the oil flushing of compressors and piping belong oil system and complete reinstatement of piping system;
10.Supervised the full execution of alignment program applied to specific rotating equipment and solved the punch list problems;
11.Supervised all the specific activities related to the rotating equipment during commissioning and start-up program;
12.Developed, implemented and supervised the Lubrication Program during pre-commissioning activities.

1.Coordinated pre-commissioning team (8 supervisor and 100 technicians) Technip/CCC/Saudi Aramco during KGP project execution;
2.Coordinated all the vendor representatives during pre-commissioning, site tests and activities;
3.Created and executed the Master Schedule plan for pre-commissioning of 5145 rotating equipments and 2570 electrical motors (12 GE-NP centrifugal compressors, 2 RotoFlow turboexpanders, 4 GE-NP steam turbine, 9 Howden hot gas blowers, 1079 process pumps (Flowserve, KSB, MiltonRoy, Goulds,etc., 94 submersible sump pump, 84 top side mixers, 316 air fin fan coolers, 2750 different power- electric motors);
4.Prepared, implemented and supervised application of pre-comm procedures, work instruction and alignment methods used for all specific rotating equipment;
5.Prepared, implemented and supervised application of pre-comm procedures, work instruction and alignment methods used for all specific rotating equipment;
6.Offered technical engineering expertise to the Technip/CCC/Saudi Aramco supervisor, Saudi Aramco/CCC foreman and technicians during execution of pre-commissioning, commissioning and start-up  activities related to the rotating equipment;
7.Responding to faults in execution of pre-comm and start-up activities, analyzed and found best technical solution and supervised repair execution;;
8.Supervised all the Solo-Run test performed with electrical motors and verified & certified all the handover documents;
9.Supervised all the activities connected to the oil flushing of the compressors and all piping belong oil system and complete reinstatement of piping system;
10.Supervised the full execution of alignment program applied to specific rotating equipments and solved the punch list problems;
11.Offered technical engineering expertise for repair of DGS of RotoFlow expander, propane pumps sealing system, oil/sealing system of 2 steam turbines and surge problems of centrifugal compressor, during start-up activities.

1.Coordinated pre-commissioning activity of 3 supervisors and 27 technicians in new Low-pressure Gas Sweetening, new Sulfur Recovery Units, new Propane Refrigeration unit, upgraded old SRU and Flare units and Sulphur Storage facilities;
2.Executed all the activities according with Project Master Plan and Schedule, and reported daily/weekly progress to Pre-comm Manager;
3.Supervised and coordinated the installation of new Feed Gas and Propane centrifugal compressor (Dresser-Rand, Elliott), air compressor (Elliott) and combustion air blowers (HV Turbo) according with API 618 and 686;
4.Supervised and coordinated the installation and pre-commissioning of  317 process centrifugal pumps (Flowserve, Goulds, Lorentz, etc.) 82 metering pumps (Milton Roy) according with API 610, API RP 686;
5.Offered technical expertise to CCC/Saudi Aramco supervisors, foreman and technicians during pre-commissioning and start-up activities;
6.Prepared and implemented oil flushing procedures for all compressors according with ISO_4406, NAS_1638, API_614 and ASTM D6439, prepared the piping system for flushing, supervised flushing activity and piping re-instatement;
7.Supervised all the Solo Run test of electrical motors according with Technip-Saudi Aramco procedures, recording the measurements and handover to proponent;
8.Created and implement Alignment procedure for rotating equipment and supervised the alignment activities, verified and certified the recorded results before handover.

1.Coordinated the Vibration Monitoring team (5 inspectors) inside of Ethylene units, Polyethylene units, Ethylene Glycol units, Utility Unit;
2.Vibration data collection and analysis, advanced on-site diagnostics on request (phase analysis, coast-downs, bump test, acceptance testing) and preparation of necessary technical reports;
3.Collected inspection data in accordance with company best practices and standards, maintain historical vibration databases and updated with current information, reported results to Maintenance manager;
4.Performed Root Cause Analysis and troubleshooting for critical rotating equipment and machinery based on vibration analysis of the equipment;
5.Create and implemented Condition Monitoring plan and schedule and coordinated execution of the activity as per approved schedule;
6.Offered technical expertise for breakdown evaluation, fault analysis, propose repair methods and supervised the repair activity in the workshop;
7.Offered technical engineering expertise for training/mentoring of new inspectors and coordinated the learning program for certification according with ASNT-TC1A;
8.Evaluated, expertise and supervised the repair of PE high-pressure compressor (Burckhardt K8) after major fault and assisted the start-up after repair;
9.Evaluated, expertise & supervised the repair for Charge Gas Compressor, Propylene & Ethylene Refrigeration centrifugal compressors.

1.Create and implemented maintenance strategies related to the stationary and rotating equipment together with ARC maintenance/inspection staff;
2.Offered full support and expertise to Plant Inspection Dept. in the development process of Inspection procedures and work instruction dedicated to all stationary, rotating, loading, storage and piping equipment;
3.Offered engineering expertise for preparation, implementation and application of NDT inspection procedures and work instruction – RT, UT, MT and PT applied to welding joints executed in workshop/on-site;
4.Offered full support for training of  NDT local operators for certification in RT, UT, MT, PT inspection according with ASNT -1 requirements;
5.Created, implemented and supervised a master maintenance program dedicated to overhaul, testing and re-rating of 14 cranes of refinery (from 14 up to 100 tf) according with BP technical requirements;
6.Evaluated, expertise and supervised the repair of the convection/radiation coil of Catalytic Reforming furnace no 2 and 3 affected by  hot cracking;
7.Evaluated, expertise and supervised the repair of main distillation tower in CDU, tower affected by corrosion problems on the top side;
8.Supervised the design, manufacture, installation, NDT inspection and testing applied to the 14 new oil storage tanks in the Tank Farm according with API 650
9.Re-design and re-rated 8 storage tanks (raw oil, gasoil, diesel, kerosene) according with API 650 – 653, tanks affected by local/general corrosion;
10.Full support and supervision for major overhaul of 3 Dresser-Rand steam turbine belong recycle gas and hydrogen make-up centrifugal compressors;
11.Evaluated, expertise and supervised the design, fabrication, inspection and installation of 10 LNG storage tanks (95 000 gallons), loading/unloading and rotating equipment and piping, in the ARC harbor area.

1.Coordinated the Turn Around Maintenance in Area 1,2,3,4 and TAM + Rehabilitation project in Area 5 (old refinery), Power Plant and Utilities;
2.Created, implemented and coordinated the Master Schedule plan for TAM in CDU, VDU (area1) NHU, CRU, KHU, CCR (area2) FCC (area3) and power plant;
3.Coordinated the Rehabilitation project in Power Plant (4 turbo-generators of 14MW and 4 steam boilers – design, fabrication, installation, SAT/FAT and start-up of the new package equipment;
4.Coordinated the NDT evaluation project related to the FCC reactor-regenerator and catalyst line, affected by corrosion and hot cracking;
5.Coordinated the repair project for the FCC regenerator- reactor-riser affected by corrosion and hot cracking;
6.Coordinated the repair project for the wet gas compressor Dresser-Rand in area 5 (new rotors, shaft, journal bearings, thrust bearings, new oil system);
7.Prepared and supervised execution of rehabilitation project of FCC compressor foundation affected by deep cracks network;
8.Coordinated engineering design of spare parts, procurement and fabrication for all necessary spare parts to be used in TAM project.

1.Preparation & Review of EPC & Engineering Technical & Commercial proposals, Inception/ Feasibility reports, FEED documents, Tender documents; Technical bid evaluation reports; Cost/Budget estimates, Contract Documents and Contract Negotiations, Claims, with keen interests in mechanical design, stress evaluation, fabrication design (welding and inspection),  design optimization, etc.
2.Evaluated of Basic / Detailed of Engineering design related to the fabrication, inspection, field testing and troubleshooting of different package stationary and rotating equipment, FAT/SAT, Plant Commissioning, Startup and Performance tests, O&M contracts;
3.Preparation of Basic & Detail Engineering Design for Retrofitting Delayed Coking Drums, Hydraulic Decoking System, Hydraulic Drilling & Cutting Tools,  Delayed Coker Furnace, Crude Distillation Furnace, Vacuum Distillation Furnace, VDU Tower and internals (Sulzer), Desalination Package (Baker-Hughes);
4.Retrofitting of coke-cutting jet pump (Vogel-Stokke), new Vertical Coke Drums, new Top and Bottom un-heading system, Hydraulic Decoking System, Combination Coke Drill & Cut Tools, retrofit Wet Gas reciprocating compressor;
5.Created a detailed work plan which identified and sequenced the activities needed to successfully complete the project;
6.Determined the necessary resources (time, money, equipment, etc) required to complete the project
7.Developed a Master Schedule for project completion that effectively allocates the resources to all the activities and supervised execution of the project according to the plan;
8.Developed necessary forms and records to document all the project activities;
9.Monitored the progress of the project and made adjustments as necessary to ensure the successful completion of the project;
10.Established a communication schedule to update stakeholders including appropriate staff in the organization on the progress of the project.

1.Performed basic/detail engineering design for revamp of Charge Gas centrifugal compressor (Olefin) -(new rotors, new shaft, new sealing system, new journal bearings, etc) including rotor-dynamics analysis, Propylene Refrigeration centrifugal compressor (Olefin), Hydrogen Make-up centrifugal compressor (CCR) according with API 617;
2.Performed basic/detail engineering design for revamp Wet Gas reciprocating compressor (DCX) – (new pistons, new piston rods, new seal packing, new gear-box) according with API_618 and API 686;
3.Prepared and supervised execution of foundation repair project of reciprocating gas compressor in Delayed Coker (Wet Gas), Catalytic Reforming-Hydrogen Make-up and Recycle gas and Polyethylene compressor, all foundation affected by deep crack network;
4.Performed rotor-dynamics analysis, design and troubleshooting for 11 centrifugal compressors, 5 steam turbines, 12 multistage pumps, providing technical consultancy and assistance for Test or Field vibration problems;
5.Performed correction of rotor-dynamic deficiencies exhibited by the existing design and prepared technical solution for improvement using the development package prepared by Department of Turbomachinery – University of Ploiesti;
6.Performed run-up, coast-down, bode and orbit plot data field collection using B & K equipment, IRD Mechanalysis software and development package of Department of Turbomachinery – University of Ploiesti.
